to hurt plenty of people.

221
00:09:57,850 --> 00:10:00,035
Point taken.

222
00:10:03,123 --> 00:10:05,157
Yeah.

223
00:10:06,826 --> 00:10:08,427
Can I help you?

224
00:10:08,429 --> 00:10:10,245
This is the, uh...

225
00:10:10,247 --> 00:10:12,414
the bomb's power source,
I presume?

226
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:13,966
Six volt.

227
00:10:13,968 --> 00:10:16,084
Very interesting company,
PrimSource Battery.

228
00:10:16,086 --> 00:10:18,170
Founded in 1888
by British expat

229
00:10:18,172 --> 00:10:19,805
and purveyor
of mechanical novelties,

230
00:10:19,807 --> 00:10:21,340
Hubert Primler.

231
00:10:21,342 --> 00:10:24,426
They switched to making
batteries full-time in 1907,

232
00:10:24,428 --> 00:10:26,428
each one stamped
with the company's

233
00:10:26,430 --> 00:10:28,647
now iconic rising-sun logo.

234
00:10:28,649 --> 00:10:30,849
The logo remained unchanged
until 2008,

235
00:10:30,851 --> 00:10:32,717
when a small oak tree was added

236
00:10:32,719 --> 00:10:34,653
to commemorate
the company's centenary.

237
00:10:34,655 --> 00:10:37,239
Yet this one has no oak tree.

238
00:10:38,158 --> 00:10:39,274
That means that battery

239
00:10:39,276 --> 00:10:41,076
is more than four years old.

240
00:10:41,078 --> 00:10:44,246
Odd, isn't it,
go to all that trouble

241
00:10:44,248 --> 00:10:45,730
building an elaborate
explosive device

242
00:10:45,732 --> 00:10:47,249
and then power it with an old

243
00:10:47,251 --> 00:10:48,750
and potentially
unreliable battery?

244
00:10:48,752 --> 00:10:51,053
Odd, yes,
but not impossible.

245
00:10:51,055 --> 00:10:53,589
Holmes, Holmes,
I've only got a few minutes here

246
00:10:53,591 --> 00:10:55,290
to pick Bennett's brain
before I have

247
00:10:55,292 --> 00:10:56,741
to stand in front
of 20 cameras

248
00:10:56,743 --> 00:10:57,909
to explain what happened
this morning.

249
00:10:57,911 --> 00:10:59,928
What about that?
What about what?

250
00:10:59,930 --> 00:11:01,763
It's the president.

251
00:11:01,765 --> 00:11:03,932
Wrong. It's the senator.
Captain...

252
00:11:03,934 --> 00:11:05,517
Senator Obama,
not President Obama.

253
00:11:05,519 --> 00:11:07,769
You can tell from the lack
of gray in his hair.

254
00:11:07,771 --> 00:11:10,189
He's right. I can make
out a date on this one.

